  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the present study was to compare the results of transanal haemorrhoidal
      dearterialisation and stapler haemorrhopidopexy in the treatment of grade III and IV
      haemorrhoids with a long-term follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
